{"type":"message","id":"42f2ef1a","parentId":"9df9d2b2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:12:53.950Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"369\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1962323981\",\n  \"sender\": \"Lucca Werner\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 21:12 GMT-3\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Lucca Werner (1962323981)\",\n  \"id\": \"1962323981\",\n  \"name\": \"Lucca Werner\"\n}\n```\n\nTobias, vamos continuar exactamente do ponto onde parámos no WebChat.\n\nContexto actual consolidado:\n\n## Estado do S4\n- S4 já tem arquitectura, runtime flow, invocation spec, contracts registry, schemas, actor docs e planning docs fechados.\n- Foundation (Phase 1) está concluída e provada.\n- Phase 2A single-target prototype está concluída.\n- 3A Brave-first discovery integration está concluída.\n- O target real usado no prototype foi o Hotel Quitandinha.\n- O pipeline S4 já provou artifact chain completa no disco:\n research_intake -> research_batch_manifest -> brief -> candidate_set -> evaluated_set -> coverage_report -> research_pack -> sector_report -> s4_completed.\n- 7/7 schema validations passaram.\n- Coverage do run real foi partially_covered.\n- Brave Search agora é o discovery primário e Firecrawl ficou como fallback/extraction.\n\n## Policy congelada\n- Browsing do S4 final:\n - Brave Search = discovery primário\n - Firecrawl = fetch/extraction/fallback\n - Playwright = fallback apenas\n- Por enquanto os agents ficam em openai-codex/gpt-5.4-mini.\n\n## Estado de modelos/auth\n- Default principal está de novo em openai-codex/gpt-5.4\n- OpenAI principal usa OAuth/Codex, não openai API key\n- Allowlist actual desejada:\n - openai-codex/gpt-5.4\n - openai-codex/gpt-5.4-mini\n - claude-cli/claude-sonnet-4-6\n - claude-cli/claude-haiku-4-5\n - claude-cli/claude-opus-4-6\n\n## Estado do Claude Code\n- Claude Code está a implementar o S4 no padrão correcto do Block 2/S3.\n- Já existe o doc:\n C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\S4_AGENT_MATERIALIZATION_PLAN.md\n- Próximo passo activo é:\n M1 — materializar oficialmente o sm_s4_asset_research como agent real OpenClaw.\n\n## Regra importante reaprendida\n- pasta/docs locais NÃO bastam para contar um agent como criado.\n- materialização real exige:\n 1. oficialização no OpenClaw\n 2. aparecer em openclaw agents list\n 3. executar turno real com sucesso\n\n## Comando relevante já confirmado\n- openclaw agents add [name] --workspace <dir> --model <id> --non-interactive\n- para o supervisor S4, o comando proposto é:\n openclaw agents add sm_s4_asset_research --workspace \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s4_asset_research\" --model openai-codex/gpt-5.4-mini --non-interactive\n\n## O que eu preciso agora\nQuero retomar exactamente daqui:\n- acompanhar a resposta do Claude Code sobre o M1\n- validar a criação/oficialização real do sm_s4_asset_research\n- rever o Gate M1\n- e continuar a coordenação contigo como architect/gate reviewer\n\nPor favor, responde já assumindo este contexto como activo, sem me fazer reexplicar do zero."}],"timestamp":1775347973931}}
{"type":"message","id":"93980ba2","parentId":"42f2ef1a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:13:10.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfeito. Assumo este contexto como activo.\n\nJá confirmei um ponto crítico: o `sm_s4_asset_research` **já aparece em `openclaw agents list`**, portanto o passo **(1) oficialização no OpenClaw** e **(2) aparecer na registry/lista** estão **passados**.\n\n### Onde estamos exactamente agora\nO estado real do M1 neste momento é:\n\n- **oficialização**: ok\n- **presença em `openclaw agents list`**: ok\n- **prova de turno real com sucesso**: **ainda é o gate em aberto**\n\nOu seja: o agent já conta como **materializado administrativamente**, mas **ainda não como M1 fechado** até provar runtime real.\n\n### Leitura correcta do Gate M1\nPelo plano, o Gate M1 exige provar:\n\n- boundary lança `sm_s4_asset_research` como actor real OpenClaw\n- supervisor faz boot em runtime real\n- supervisor executa **pelo menos o primeiro dispatch válido**\n- supervisor escreve **status/checkpoints esperados** em runtime real\n\nPortanto, eu fecharia o gate só quando tivermos evidência concreta destes 4 pontos — idealmente no disco + logs de execução.\n\n### O que eu proponho como próximo passo imediato\nAgora o movimento certo é este, por ordem:\n\n1. **receber/ver a resposta do Claude Code sobre o M1**\n   - o que ele já materializou\n   - que command path está a usar para invocação real\n   - que artefactos/status espera escrever no primeiro run\n\n2. **fazer a validação de runtime**\n   - lançar um turno real do `sm_s4_asset_research`\n   - verificar se:\n     - arranca mesmo como actor OpenClaw\n     - entra no fluxo S4 correcto\n     - faz o primeiro dispatch válido\n     - escreve os artefactos/checkpoints esperados\n\n3. **revisão de gate**\n   - se houver boot mas sem dispatch: M1 ainda não fecha\n   - se houver dispatch mas sem checkpoint/status canónicos: M1 ainda não fecha\n   - só fecha quando o boundary actor + runtime evidence + first dispatch + persisted state estiverem todos provados\n\n### Minha leitura arquitectural\nA boa notícia é que o risco mais chato já caiu: **não estamos mais na zona ambígua de “pasta existe mas actor não existe”**.\n\nAgora a discussão deixa de ser “foi criado?” e passa a ser a discussão certa:\n\n- o supervisor está **realmente vivo no substrate**\n- o handoff supervisor/runtime está correcto\n- o S4 entrou no padrão validado do B2/S3\n- o bridge temporário, se existir, está explícito e controlado\n\n### Conclusão curta\n**Status actual do M1: em progresso avançado, mas ainda não aprovado.**\nA oficialização do `sm_s4_asset_research` está validada.\nO que falta é a **prova operacional real do primeiro turno**.\n\nSe quiser, no próximo passo eu posso fazer uma de duas coisas contigo:\n\n- **modo reviewer**: tu colas aqui a resposta/output do Claude Code e eu faço gate review em cima disso\n- **modo executor-reviewer**: eu próprio corro a validação local do M1 agora e digo-te exactamente se passa ou falha, com base em evidência real\n\nSe queres, eu avanço já para a **validação operacional do M1**.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a90979d88191b50a0c7d2fc72a58\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":22237,"output":738,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22975,"cost":{"input":0.0555925,"output":0.01107,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0666625}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775347973949,"responseId":"resp_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a90715288191a520a7c446886061"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5fc77e5e","parentId":"93980ba2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:40.822Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"371\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1962323981\",\n  \"sender\": \"Lucca Werner\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 21:14 GMT-3\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Lucca Werner (1962323981)\",\n  \"id\": \"1962323981\",\n  \"name\": \"Lucca Werner\"\n}\n```\n\nClaude code mandou: Faz sentido. Resumo pro Tobias:\nM1 — Materialização do sm_s4_asset_research\nO que foi feito (steps 1-4 de 5)\n 1. Agent criado: openclaw agents add sm_s4_asset_research --model openai-codex/gpt-5.4-mini\n 2. Confirmado: aparece no openclaw agents list\n 3. Docs materializados: MISSION, CONTRACT, OPERATIONS, IDENTITY, SOUL, TOOLS, CONTEXT (8 docs criados/reescritos, seguindo padrão do SM S3)\n 4. Boundary atualizado: w3_block2.py agora usa _launch_openclaw_agent(\"sm_s4_asset_research\", ...) — mesmo padrão do S3\nO que o Tobias precisa validar\n ∙ MISSION.md — boot + bridge dispatch + validation + closure\n ∙ CONTRACT.md — bootstrap contract completo (19 campos), failure table, fresh-session rule\n ∙ OPERATIONS.md — 20 steps com exec python commands exatos pros helpers\n ∙ TOOLS.md — 11 helpers listados com paths\nFicheiros em: C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s4_asset_research\\\nO que falta (step 5)\nGate M1 proof em runtime real — rodar o boundary e provar que o SM OpenClaw faz boot + primeiro dispatch."}],"timestamp":1775348080798}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3737003","parentId":"5fc77e5e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:45.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ucO8LFRUnJAzD6PavuIOHNjB|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a7c81919258a080b2ca8405","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s4_asset_research\\MISSION.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s4_asset_research\\\\MISSION.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7TotGXY0GgCsxYBOMvreNa6A|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a8c81918981fb27ba8c89a2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s4_asset_research\\CONTRACT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s4_asset_research\\\\CONTRACT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MSnqq1fK09ppiJZXiG4lwfMq|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a948191be3fbcba7abcb462","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s4_asset_research\\OPERATIONS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s4_asset_research\\\\OPERATIONS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OcpHRyjUhQTFll659imN4orJ|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a988191a706cd26c9919629","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s4_asset_research\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s4_asset_research\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":602,"output":162,"cacheRead":22784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23548,"cost":{"input":0.001505,"output":0.00243,"cacheRead":0.005696,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009631}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775348080821,"responseId":"resp_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a97227b88191adbcf9c742c4c56e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"819429ba","parentId":"a3737003","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:45.767Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ucO8LFRUnJAzD6PavuIOHNjB|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a7c81919258a080b2ca8405","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MISSION.md\n\nA tua missao e assumir o controlo operativo do sector S4 para um unico job, com contexto limpo por activacao.\n\nDeves:\n- validar o bootstrap recebido (`s4.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`)\n- assumir formalmente o sector\n- criar a estrutura de directorias do S4 usando helper: `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\dirs.py\" <sector_root>`\n- despachar operators sequencialmente usando bridge execution (helpers) na fase M1\n- para bridge M1: invocar helpers directamente via exec, e.g.: `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\target_builder.py\" <args>`\n- validar que outputs existem e sao schema-valid usando: `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\schema_validator.py\" <artifact_path> <schema_name>`\n- escrever checkpoints usando: `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\checkpoint_writer.py\" <args>`\n- obedecer rigidamente ao operator registry canonico do S4\n- nao absorver internamente o trabalho dos operators como output final do sector\n- usar exactamente os paths declarados no bootstrap como source of truth, sem reconstruir paths por heuristica textual\n- preservar literalmente os paths recebidos, incluindo caracteres Unicode especiais, e nao normalizar para variantes \"parecidas\"\n- monitorizar outputs por artefactos persistidos\n- validar outputs estruturais\n- espelhar obrigatoriamente o resultado macro no `b2_root/checkpoints/` (`s4_completed.json` ou `s4_failed.json`)\n- escrever checkpoint final de sucesso, degradacao ou falha\n\nNunca deves depender de memoria conversacional residual.\nO disco e a fonte de verdade.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348085750}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d5a1f86","parentId":"819429ba","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:45.785Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7TotGXY0GgCsxYBOMvreNa6A|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a8c81918981fb27ba8c89a2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTRACT.md\n\n## Bootstrap input\nLes um payload compativel com `s4.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`.\n\nCampos obrigatorios:\n- `kind = s4_start`\n- `contract_version = s4.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`\n- `job_id`\n- `video_id`\n- `account_id`\n- `language`\n- `run_root`\n- `b2_root`\n- `sector_root`\n- `upstream.compiled_entities_path`\n- `upstream.sector_report_path`\n- `checkpoints_dir`\n- `dispatch_dir`\n- `intake_dir`\n- `targets_dir`\n- `compiled_dir`\n- `logs_dir`\n- `runtime_dir`\n\n## Path handling rule\nTodos os paths recebidos no bootstrap devem ser tratados como literais e canonicos para aquele run.\n\nRegras obrigatorias:\n- nao reconstruir paths a partir de fragmentos textuais ou nomes de pasta\n- nao substituir caracteres Unicode \"parecidos\" (ex.: `---` por `-`)\n- nao trocar o root do sector por um root derivado do workspace local do agent\n- se um path do bootstrap nao existir, falhar explicitamente em vez de improvisar outro path\n\n## Outputs obrigatorios\n- artefacto de arranque do supervisor\n- dispatch artifacts por operator\n- checkpoint files por fase\n- `compiled/s4_research_pack.json`\n- `compiled/s4_sector_report.md`\n- `checkpoints/s4_sector_completed.json` ou `checkpoints/s4_sector_failed.json`\n- espelho macro obrigatorio em `b2_root/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` ou `b2_root/checkpoints/s4_failed.json`\n\n## Success rule\nSo fechas o sector como concluido quando os artefactos finais existirem e estiverem estruturalmente coerentes.\n\nSucesso sectorial so conta como pronto para o bloco quando:\n- `s4_research_pack.json` existir no disco\n- `s4_sector_report.md` existir no disco\n- schema validation passar em ambos\n- o checkpoint macro `b2_root/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` tiver sido escrito no root correcto do run\n\n## Canonical operator list\nPara a fase actual do S4, o supervisor so pode tratar estes 6 operators como canonicos:\n- `op_s4_target_builder`\n- `op_s4_web_investigator`\n- `op_s4_target_research_worker`\n- `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n- `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n- `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\n## Failure rule\nSe faltar precondicao critica, falha explicitamente e persiste o checkpoint de falha.\n\nTabela de decisao V1:\n- `op_s4_target_builder` falha -> sector falha\n- `op_s4_web_investigator` falha -> sector falha\n- um ou mais `op_s4_target_research_worker` runs falham -> continuar com outputs disponiveis; coverage e final pack devem reflectir os gaps explicitamente\n- `op_s4_candidate_evaluator` falha -> sector falha\n- `op_s4_coverage_analyst` falha -> sector falha\n- `op_s4_pack_compiler` falha -> sector falha\n\nSe o supervisor fizer trabalho de operator internamente em vez de despachar os operators canonicos, isso deve ser tratado como violacao do contract actual, nao como sucesso do sector.\n\n## Fresh-session rule for operator launches\nCada invoke do supervisor para operator deve usar um `session-id` unico por run e por operator.\n\nObjectivo:\n- evitar acumulacao de contexto entre videos\n- evitar bleed entre activacoes de operators diferentes\n- reduzir custo inutil de transcripts longas\n\nExemplo conceptual de naming:\n- `s4-<job_id>-target_builder-<run_token>`\n- `s4-<job_id>-web_investigator-<run_token>`\n- `s4-<job_id>-research_worker-<target_id>-<run_token>`\n- `s4-<job_id>-evaluator-<run_token>`\n- `s4-<job_id>-coverage-<run_token>`\n- `s4-<job_id>-pack_compiler-<run_token>`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348085768}}
{"type":"message","id":"abfd5285","parentId":"4d5a1f86","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:45.803Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MSnqq1fK09ppiJZXiG4lwfMq|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a948191be3fbcba7abcb462","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OPERATIONS.md\n\n## Regras operacionais\n\n1. Contexto limpo por activacao.\n2. Estado no disco > conversa.\n3. Falha explicita > sucesso ambiguo.\n4. Nao inventar outputs inexistentes.\n5. Nao considerar um operator concluido apenas por resposta textual.\n\n## Sequencia base\n\n1. Ler bootstrap do path recebido na activation message.\n2. Validar campos do bootstrap e confirmar que upstream paths existem (compiled_entities_path).\n3. Criar directorias do S4:\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\dirs.py\" <sector_root>`\n4. Escrever sector_status (phase=bootstrap, status=started):\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\checkpoint_writer.py\" started <sector_root> <job_id>`\n5. Dispatch target_builder:\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\target_builder.py\" <compiled_entities_path> <sector_root> <job_id> <video_id> <account_id> <language>`\n6. Validar que intake existe e schema-validates:\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\schema_validator.py\" <intake_path> research_intake`\n7. Gerar batch manifest:\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\batch_manifest_builder.py\" <intake_path> <sector_root>`\n8. Validar manifest:\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\schema_validator.py\" <manifest_path> research_batch_manifest`\n9. Dispatch web_investigator:\n   `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\web_investigator.py\" <intake_path> <manifest_path> <sector_root>`\n10. Validar que briefs existem no disco.\n11. Dispatch research_worker(s) — um por target brief:\n    `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\research_worker.py\" <brief_path> <sector_root>`\n12. Validar que candidate_sets existem no disco.\n13. Dispatch candidate_evaluator:\n    `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\candidate_evaluator.py\" <candidate_set_path> <brief_path> <sector_root>`\n14. Validar que evaluated candidate sets existem.\n15. Dispatch coverage_analyst:\n    `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\coverage_analyst.py\" <intake_path> <sector_root>`\n16. Validar que coverage report existe.\n17. Dispatch pack_compiler:\n    `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\pack_compiler.py\" <intake_path> <sector_root> <job_id> <video_id> <account_id> <language>`\n18. Validar que final pack (`s4_research_pack.json`) e sector report (`s4_sector_report.md`) existem.\n19. Escrever completion checkpoint:\n    `exec python \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\checkpoint_writer.py\" completed <sector_root> <job_id> <compiled_output_path> <report_path>`\n20. Verificar que B2 mirror existe em `b2_root/checkpoints/s4_completed.json`.\n\n## Bridge policy (M1)\n\nNa fase M1, todos os operator dispatches usam bridge execution via helpers Python.\nIsto transitara progressivamente para real OpenClaw agent invocations em M2.\n\n## Limites\n\n- nao es boundary Paperclip-facing\n- nao es o `b2_director`\n- nao deves delegar compile final para os operators sem validacao\n- nao deves chamar operators fora do registry oficial\n- nao deves fazer o trabalho semantico dos operators internamente como substituto do dispatch real\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348085785}}
{"type":"message","id":"02747835","parentId":"abfd5285","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:45.826Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_OcpHRyjUhQTFll659imN4orJ|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9760a988191a706cd26c9919629","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md\n\n## Helper tools disponiveis\n\nTodos os helpers estao em:\n`C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\`\n\nInvocacao: `exec python \"<helper_path>\" <args>`\n\n### dirs.py\nCria a estrutura de directorias do S4 (intake, targets, compiled, checkpoints, dispatch, logs, runtime).\n\n### target_builder.py\nConstroi research intake a partir das compiled entities do S3.\n\n### batch_manifest_builder.py\nGera batch manifest a partir do intake (define batches, ordering, parallelism cap).\n\n### web_investigator.py\nConstroi target research briefs com search goals e storage paths.\n\n### research_worker.py\nExecuta web research via Brave Search + Firecrawl para um target. Produz candidate_set.\n\n### candidate_evaluator.py\nAvalia candidatos contra o brief. Produz evaluated_candidate_set com classificacoes finais.\n\n### coverage_analyst.py\nAnalise heuristica de cobertura — target-level e scene-level. Produz coverage_report.\n\n### pack_compiler.py\nCompila final pack (`s4_research_pack.json`) + sector report (`s4_sector_report.md`).\n\n### schema_validator.py\nValida artefactos contra JSON schemas definidos. Retorna pass/fail + erros.\n\n### checkpoint_writer.py\nEscreve checkpoints de status, completion e failure. Inclui B2 mirror.\n\n### bootstrap_loader.py\nCarrega e valida o bootstrap do supervisor. Retorna campos parsed ou erro.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348085803}}
{"type":"message","id":"498a13c4","parentId":"02747835","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:50.472Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou rever os docs do agente e depois tentar a prova operacional do Gate M1 em runtime real.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a977ec3881919271765cd0863e8e\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_LoiJRCiv2b4AjpHkPB2LyU7R|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a97b15448191b91cbf3a1f3dc242","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw agent --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oYdI6Nlu1gHLKMDxFYObqhxK|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a97b15548191b9e974fbd5d5b6ff","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rg -n \"_launch_openclaw_agent|sm_s4_asset_research|s4.supervisor_bootstrap.v1|s4_start\" \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"rg -n \\\"_launch_openclaw_agent|sm_s4_asset_research|s4.supervisor_bootstrap.v1|s4_start\\\" \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2690,"output":175,"cacheRead":23424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26289,"cost":{"input":0.006725000000000001,"output":0.002625,"cacheRead":0.005856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015206}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775348085824,"responseId":"resp_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a976fb4c819189cb0042707fc3a0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a078992","parentId":"498a13c4","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:14:54.755Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_LoiJRCiv2b4AjpHkPB2LyU7R|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a97b15448191b91cbf3a1f3dc242","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.2 (d74a122) — I'm not saying your workflow is chaotic... I'm just bringing a linter and a helmet.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4102,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.2 (d74a122) — I'm not saying your workflow is chaotic... I'm just bringing a linter and a helmet.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348094738}}
