{"type":"message","id":"99f44e14","parentId":"50c69837","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:22.455Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_djMK7Op6Oc3TCIjA5VBw6eSv|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a99aa02c81919c1c19f926adf32c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# sm_s4_asset_research\n\n_Status: planning draft_\n_Last updated: 2026-04-04_\n_Actor type: sector supervisor_\n_Sector: S4 — Asset Research_\n\n---\n\n## 1. Role\n\n`sm_s4_asset_research` is the **sector supervisor** for S4.\n\nIt is the owner of sector-level progression, gating, dispatch, validation, and closure.\n\nIt is **not** the actor that should personally perform the work of:\n- target building\n- web discovery\n- candidate evaluation\n- coverage analysis\n- pack compilation\n\nIts job is to govern those steps through artifact-based control.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Core mission\n\nTake S4 from:\n- requested sector with valid S3 upstream artifacts\n\nto:\n- completed / failed S4 sector with validated final outputs and checkpoints\n\nusing the proven B2/S3 runtime pattern.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Inputs\n\nPrimary runtime inputs:\n- `s4.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`\n- upstream `compiled_entities.json`\n- upstream `s3_sector_report.md` when available\n- sector runtime directories / roots\n\nDownstream-produced inputs during sector life:\n- `s4_research_intake.json`\n- `research_batch_manifest.json`\n- `target_research_brief.json` files\n- `candidate_set.json` files\n- `evaluated_candidate_set.json` files\n- `coverage_report.json`\n- `s4_research_pack.json`\n- `s4_sector_report.md`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Outputs\n\nSupervisor-owned outputs:\n- sector runtime status updates\n- sector dispatch artifacts\n- checkpoint files\n- completion/failure macro checkpoint\n- B2 checkpoint mirroring\n\nIt does **not** own the semantic content of operator output artifacts, but it owns their orchestration and validation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Responsibilities\n\n## 5.1 Bootstrap responsibilities\n- read bootstrap artifact\n- validate required paths and upstream refs\n- confirm S3 upstream artifact presence\n- assume sector ownership\n- initialize runtime state\n\n## 5.2 Dispatch responsibilities\n- dispatch `op_s4_target_builder`\n- dispatch `op_s4_web_investigator`\n- dispatch `op_s4_target_research_worker` runs\n- dispatch `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n- dispatch `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n- dispatch `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\n## 5.3 Validation responsibilities\n- validate intake existence and schema-level sufficiency\n- validate brief generation completion\n- validate candidate set presence\n- validate evaluated outputs\n- validate coverage report\n- validate final pack and sector report\n\n## 5.4 Control-flow responsibilities\n- govern phase transitions\n- maintain runtime state/checkpoints\n- enforce v1 single-pass policy\n- decide completion / failure / degraded completion policy if later adopted explicitly\n\n## 5.5 Closure responsibilities\n- write `s4_completed.json` or `s4_failed.json`\n- mirror final checkpoint into B2 checkpoints\n- ensure `s4_research_pack.json` and `s4_sector_report.md` both exist before completion\n\n---\n\n## 6. What this actor must NOT do\n\n- must not absorb target-builder work directly\n- must not act as a freeform discovery researcher\n- must not manually evaluate every candidate in place of evaluator\n- must not treat conversational outputs as source of truth over disk artifacts\n- must not rely on nested spawn trees in the critical path\n- must not close the sector based only on process exit codes\n\n---\n\n## 7. Runtime behavior\n\n## 7.1 Invocation posture\n- launched by boundary after `s4_requested.json`\n- runs as the sector owner for the duration of S4\n- dispatches discrete operators through the proven runtime primitive\n\n## 7.2 State ownership\nThis actor is the primary owner of S4 runtime state progression.\n\nIt should keep sector control on disk, not in implicit memory.\n\n## 7.3 Completion truth model\nCompletion depends on:\n- final pack exists\n- sector report exists\n- checkpoints written\n- validation passes\n\nNot on:\n- operator verbal summaries\n- process exit code alone\n\n---\n\n## 8. Decision model\n\nThe supervisor's job is not to make every semantic judgment in the sector.\nIts job is to make **control decisions** such as:\n\n- can S4 start?\n- is intake valid enough?\n- are briefs present?\n- did workers produce the expected outputs?\n- can evaluation start?\n- can coverage analysis start?\n- can final compilation start?\n- can the sector close?\n\nIt should consume summaries/artifacts, not raw unbounded discovery context.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Failure handling posture\n\nThe supervisor should be strict about missing critical artifacts.\n\nExamples of failure-worthy conditions:\n- missing bootstrap essentials\n- missing upstream compiled artifact\n- missing intake after target builder success claim\n- missing final pack or sector report at closure\n- malformed checkpoint/output contract in critical path\n\nExamples of non-fatal but warning-worthy conditions:\n- zero candidates for some targets\n- partially covered targets\n- failed file materialization on some candidates\n- inspiration-only outcomes\n\n### 9.1 V1 operator failure decision table\n\n- `op_s4_target_builder` fails -> sector fails\n- `op_s4_web_investigator` fails -> sector fails\n- one or more `op_s4_target_research_worker` runs fail -> continue with available outputs; coverage and final pack must reflect the gaps explicitly\n- `op_s4_candidate_evaluator` fails -> sector fails\n- `op_s4_coverage_analyst` fails -> sector fails\n- `op_s4_pack_compiler` fails -> sector fails\n\n---\n\n## 10. Interfaces with other actors\n\n### With `b2_director`\n- receives sector request indirectly through bootstrap + boundary launch\n- returns sector completion/failure via checkpoints\n\n### With `op_s4_target_builder`\n- dispatches it\n- validates intake/report\n\n### With `op_s4_web_investigator`\n- dispatches it\n- consumes target briefs / optional batch summaries\n\n### With `op_s4_target_research_worker`\n- dispatches worker runs after briefs exist\n- validates presence of candidate sets and target-local files\n\n### With `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n- dispatches evaluator phase\n- validates evaluated candidate sets\n\n### With `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n- dispatches coverage phase\n- validates coverage report\n\n### With `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n- dispatches final compiler\n- validates final pack and sector report\n\n---\n\n## 11. Key risks for this actor\n\n- becoming a semantic super-hero instead of a control actor\n- absorbing too much raw discovery context\n- silently accepting missing artifacts\n- allowing vague completion semantics\n- mixing logical hierarchy with runtime process hierarchy\n\n---\n\n## 12. Success criteria\n\nThis actor is successful when:\n- S4 progresses phase by phase through disk-backed artifacts\n- all required operators are dispatched in order\n- invalid/missing artifacts are caught early\n- the final sector closes only with both final outputs present\n- B2 can resume deterministically from the mirrored final checkpoint\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348122437}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5d587dd","parentId":"99f44e14","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:27.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_nT8neOm9hq8p3bUaCNJKZoqv|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a046108191ac90c11a2a77c732","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\helpers\\real_run_s3_supervisor_one_operator_cli.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\helpers\\\\real_run_s3_supervisor_one_operator_cli.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Z4MsiII4vk1tJ6G8Uup1PjrD|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a04624819195f45ca918236e43","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\run_single_target.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4\\\\helpers\\\\run_single_target.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5Ao4yX9NbzXpTQoFHY6ZrHQc|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a0462c819188b1815ee5763457","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\supervisor_shell.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4\\\\helpers\\\\supervisor_shell.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1666,"output":146,"cacheRead":30336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32148,"cost":{"input":0.004165,"output":0.00219,"cacheRead":0.007584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013939}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775348122457,"responseId":"resp_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a99b57d8819184551243fe9a6ac7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4219e573","parentId":"f5d587dd","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:28.249Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_nT8neOm9hq8p3bUaCNJKZoqv|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a046108191ac90c11a2a77c732","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import json\nimport shutil\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nBASE = Path(r\"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\")\n\n\ndef utc_now():\n    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n\n\ndef run_py(script: Path, *args: str, check=True):\n    cmd = [sys.executable, str(script), *args]\n    result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)\n    if check and result.returncode != 0:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"script failed: {script}\\nstdout={result.stdout}\\nstderr={result.stderr}\")\n    return result\n\n\ndef write_json(path: Path, data: dict):\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    path.write_text(json.dumps(data, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) != 2:\n        raise SystemExit(\"usage: real_run_s3_supervisor_one_operator_cli.py <run_root>\")\n\n    run_root = Path(sys.argv[1])\n    b2_root = run_root / \"b2\"\n    if run_root.exists():\n        shutil.rmtree(run_root)\n    run_root.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    screenplay = {\n        \"video_context\": {\"title\": \"Supervisor CLI Narrow Run\"},\n        \"script_overview\": {\"summary\": \"Narrow run for real supervisor->operator CLI path\"},\n        \"scenes\": [{\"scene_id\": \"scene_001\", \"title\": \"Opening\", \"summary\": \"A palace scene with a king and a crown.\"}]\n    }\n\n    b2_bootstrap = {\n        \"kind\": \"b2_start\",\n        \"contract_version\": \"b2.bootstrap.v1\",\n        \"job_id\": \"real_supervisor_cli_001\",\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"b2_root\": str(b2_root),\n        \"account_id\": \"006\",\n        \"language\": \"pt-BR\",\n        \"inputs\": {\n            \"screenplay_analysis_path\": str(run_root / \"upstream\" / \"screenplay_analysis.json\")\n        },\n        \"mode\": \"s3_only\"\n    }\n\n    write_json(run_root / \"upstream\" / \"screenplay_analysis.json\", screenplay)\n    write_json(run_root / \"b2_bootstrap.json\", b2_bootstrap)\n\n    run_py(BASE / \"helpers\" / \"b2_state_helper.py\", \"bootstrap\", str(b2_root), \"s3_only\")\n    write_json(b2_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"b2_bootstrap_ready.json\", {\n        \"event\": \"b2_bootstrap_ready\",\n        \"job_id\": b2_bootstrap[\"job_id\"],\n        \"created_at\": utc_now()\n    })\n\n    run_py(BASE / \"helpers\" / \"build_s3_bootstrap_from_b2.py\", str(run_root / \"b2_bootstrap.json\"), str(run_root))\n    bootstrap_path = run_root / \"s3_supervisor_bootstrap.json\"\n\n    bootstrap = json.loads(bootstrap_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    sector_root = Path(bootstrap[\"sector_root\"])\n    checkpoints_dir = Path(bootstrap[\"checkpoints_dir\"])\n\n    write_json(checkpoints_dir / \"s3_supervisor_started.json\", {\n        \"event\": \"s3_supervisor_started\",\n        \"job_id\": bootstrap[\"job_id\"],\n        \"started_at\": utc_now(),\n        \"bootstrap_path\": str(bootstrap_path)\n    })\n\n    run_py(BASE / \"S3\" / \"helpers\" / \"build_operator_dispatches.py\", str(bootstrap_path), \"human_subject_extractor\")\n\n    dispatch_path = Path(bootstrap[\"dispatch_dir\"]) / \"human_subject_extractor_job.json\"\n    invoke = run_py(BASE / \"S3\" / \"helpers\" / \"invoke_operator_via_cli.py\", \"human_subject_extractor\", str(dispatch_path), check=False)\n    write_json(checkpoints_dir / \"operator_cli_invoke_result.json\", {\n        \"returncode\": invoke.returncode,\n        \"stdout\": invoke.stdout,\n        \"stderr\": invoke.stderr,\n        \"captured_at\": utc_now()\n    })\n    if invoke.returncode != 0:\n        write_json(checkpoints_dir / \"s3_final_checkpoint.json\", {\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"reason\": \"operator_cli_invoke_failed\",\n            \"captured_at\": utc_now()\n        })\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"operator invocation failed\\nstdout={invoke.stdout}\\nstderr={invoke.stderr}\")\n\n    output_path = sector_root / \"operators\" / \"human_subject_extractor\" / \"output.json\"\n    run_py(BASE / \"S3\" / \"helpers\" / \"validate_operator_output.py\", \"human_subject_extractor\", str(output_path), str(BASE / \"S3\" / \"schemas\" / \"human_subject_output.schema.json\"))\n\n    compiled_path = sector_root / \"compiled\" / \"compiled_entities.json\"\n    report_path = sector_root / \"compiled\" / \"s3_sector_report.md\"\n    run_py(BASE / \"S3\" / \"helpers\" / \"compile_s3_entities.py\", str(sector_root), str(sector_root / \"inputs\" / \"s3_source_package.json\"), str(compiled_path))\n    run_py(BASE / \"S3\" / \"helpers\" / \"generate_s3_sector_report.py\", str(compiled_path), str(report_path))\n\n    compiled = json.loads(compiled_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    status = compiled.get(\"status\")\n    write_json(checkpoints_dir / \"s3_final_checkpoint.json\", {\n        \"status\": status,\n        \"compiled_entities_path\": str(compiled_path),\n        \"sector_report_path\": str(report_path),\n        \"captured_at\": utc_now(),\n        \"primitive\": \"exec + openclaw agent --agent ... --json\"\n    })\n\n    print(json.dumps({\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"status\": status,\n        \"compiled_entities\": str(compiled_path),\n        \"report\": str(report_path)\n    }, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348128228}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4463d66","parentId":"4219e573","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:28.267Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Z4MsiII4vk1tJ6G8Uup1PjrD|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a04624819195f45ca918236e43","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"S4 Single-Target Prototype Runner -- runs full S4 pipeline for 1 target.\"\"\"\nimport sys\nimport traceback\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom artifact_io import read_json\nfrom checkpoint_writer import write_completion, write_failure\nfrom dirs import create_s4_directories\nfrom paths import (\n    sector_root as derive_sector_root,\n    intake_path,\n    batch_manifest_path,\n    target_brief_path,\n    candidate_set_path,\n    evaluated_set_path,\n    coverage_report_path,\n    research_pack_path,\n    sector_report_path,\n)\nfrom schema_validator import validate_artifact_strict\n\n\ndef _step(step_num: int, name: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Print step banner.\"\"\"\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"  STEP {step_num}: {name}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n\n\ndef run_pipeline(\n    compiled_entities_path: Path,\n    b2_root: Path,\n    job_id: str,\n    video_id: str,\n    account_id: str,\n    language: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run the full S4 single-target pipeline.\n\n    Sequence:\n    1. Create S4 directories\n    2. target_builder -> validate intake\n    3. batch_manifest_builder -> validate manifest\n    4. web_investigator -> validate briefs\n    5. research_worker -> validate candidate_set\n    6. candidate_evaluator -> validate evaluated_set\n    7. coverage_analyst -> validate coverage_report\n    8. pack_compiler -> validate research_pack\n    9. Write s4_completed checkpoint\n    \"\"\"\n    sr = derive_sector_root(b2_root)\n    compiled_entities_path = compiled_entities_path.resolve()\n\n    print(f\"\\nS4 Single-Target Prototype Runner\")\n    print(f\"  compiled_entities: {compiled_entities_path}\")\n    print(f\"  b2_root: {b2_root}\")\n    print(f\"  sector_root: {sr}\")\n    print(f\"  job_id: {job_id}\")\n    print(f\"  video_id: {video_id}\")\n    print(f\"  account_id: {account_id}\")\n    print(f\"  language: {language}\")\n\n    try:\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 1: Create S4 directories\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(1, \"Create S4 directories\")\n        create_s4_directories(sr)\n        print(f\"[runner] directories created at {sr}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 2: Target Builder\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(2, \"Target Builder\")\n        from target_builder import build_intake\n        intake_out = build_intake(\n            compiled_entities_path=compiled_entities_path,\n            sector_root=sr,\n            job_id=job_id,\n            video_id=video_id,\n            account_id=account_id,\n            language=language,\n        )\n        intake_data = read_json(intake_out)\n        validate_artifact_strict(intake_data, \"research_intake\")\n        print(f\"[runner] intake validated: {intake_out}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 3: Batch Manifest Builder\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(3, \"Batch Manifest Builder\")\n        from batch_manifest_builder import build_manifest\n        manifest_out = build_manifest(intake_out, sr)\n        manifest_data = read_json(manifest_out)\n        validate_artifact_strict(manifest_data, \"research_batch_manifest\")\n        print(f\"[runner] manifest validated: {manifest_out}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 4: Web Investigator\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(4, \"Web Investigator\")\n        from web_investigator import build_all_briefs\n        briefs = build_all_briefs(intake_out, manifest_out, sr)\n        for brief in briefs:\n            validate_artifact_strict(brief, \"target_research_brief\")\n        print(f\"[runner] {len(briefs)} briefs validated\")\n\n        # Get target IDs for subsequent steps\n        target_ids = [t[\"target_id\"] for t in intake_data[\"research_targets\"]]\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 5: Research Worker\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(5, \"Research Worker\")\n        from research_worker import research_target\n        for tid in target_ids:\n            brief_path = target_brief_path(sr, tid)\n            cs_out = research_target(brief_path, sr)\n            cs_data = read_json(cs_out)\n            validate_artifact_strict(cs_data, \"candidate_set\")\n            print(f\"[runner] candidate_set validated for {tid}: {cs_out}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 6: Candidate Evaluator\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(6, \"Candidate Evaluator\")\n        from candidate_evaluator import evaluate_candidates\n        for tid in target_ids:\n            cs_path = candidate_set_path(sr, tid)\n            brief_path = target_brief_path(sr, tid)\n            ev_out = evaluate_candidates(cs_path, brief_path, sr)\n            ev_data = read_json(ev_out)\n            validate_artifact_strict(ev_data, \"evaluated_candidate_set\")\n            print(f\"[runner] evaluated_set validated for {tid}: {ev_out}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 7: Coverage Analyst\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(7, \"Coverage Analyst\")\n        from coverage_analyst import analyze_coverage\n        cov_out = analyze_coverage(intake_out, sr)\n        cov_data = read_json(cov_out)\n        validate_artifact_strict(cov_data, \"coverage_report\")\n        print(f\"[runner] coverage report validated: {cov_out}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 8: Pack Compiler\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(8, \"Pack Compiler\")\n        from pack_compiler import compile_pack\n        pack_out = compile_pack(\n            intake_path_arg=intake_out,\n            sector_root=sr,\n            job_id=job_id,\n            video_id=video_id,\n            account_id=account_id,\n            language=language,\n        )\n        pack_data = read_json(pack_out)\n        validate_artifact_strict(pack_data, \"research_pack\")\n        print(f\"[runner] research pack validated: {pack_out}\")\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Step 9: Write s4_completed checkpoint + mirror to b2\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        _step(9, \"Completion checkpoint\")\n        report_out = sector_report_path(sr)\n        write_completion(sr, job_id, str(pack_out), str(report_out))\n\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        # Success summary\n        # -------------------------------------------------------\n        print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n        print(f\"  S4 PIPELINE COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY\")\n        print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n        print(f\"  research_pack: {pack_out}\")\n        print(f\"  sector_report: {report_out}\")\n        print(f\"  status: {pack_data['metadata']['status']}\")\n        print(f\"  targets: {len(pack_data['target_results'])}\")\n        print(f\"  scenes: {len(pack_data['scene_results'])}\")\n        print(f\"  unresolved_gaps: {len(pack_data['unresolved_gaps'])}\")\n        print(f\"{'='*60}\\n\")\n\n    except Exception as exc:\n        print(f\"\\n[runner] PIPELINE FAILED: {exc}\")\n        traceback.print_exc()\n        try:\n            write_failure(sr, job_id, str(exc)[:500])\n        except Exception:\n            print(\"[runner] could not write failure checkpoint\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) != 7:\n        raise SystemExit(\n            \"usage: run_single_target.py <compiled_entities_path> <b2_root> \"\n            \"<job_id> <video_id> <account_id> <language>\"\n        )\n    run_pipeline(\n        compiled_entities_path=Path(sys.argv[1]),\n        b2_root=Path(sys.argv[2]),\n        job_id=sys.argv[3],\n        video_id=sys.argv[4],\n        account_id=sys.argv[5],\n        language=sys.argv[6],\n    )\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348128249}}
{"type":"message","id":"c43c9d27","parentId":"b4463d66","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:28.294Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5Ao4yX9NbzXpTQoFHY6ZrHQc|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a0462c819188b1815ee5763457","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Minimal S4 supervisor shell. Boot, validate, init dirs, write status, exit.\"\"\"\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom bootstrap_loader import load_bootstrap\nfrom dirs import create_s4_directories\nfrom checkpoint_writer import write_sector_status, write_checkpoint\n\n\ndef run_supervisor(bootstrap_path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Boot the S4 supervisor: load, validate, init dirs, write status, exit.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Load + validate bootstrap\n    bootstrap = load_bootstrap(bootstrap_path)\n    sr = Path(bootstrap[\"sector_root\"]).resolve()\n    job_id = bootstrap[\"job_id\"]\n\n    print(f\"[s4-supervisor] bootstrap loaded: job_id={job_id}\")\n\n    # 2. Create S4 directories\n    create_s4_directories(sr)\n    print(f\"[s4-supervisor] directories created: {sr}\")\n\n    # 3. Write initial sector_status\n    write_sector_status(sr, phase=\"bootstrap\", status=\"started\", details={\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"video_id\": bootstrap[\"video_id\"],\n        \"account_id\": bootstrap[\"account_id\"],\n        \"language\": bootstrap[\"language\"],\n    })\n    print(\"[s4-supervisor] sector_status written: phase=bootstrap, status=started\")\n\n    # 4. Write initial checkpoint\n    write_checkpoint(sr, event=\"s4_bootstrap_started\", data={\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n    })\n    print(\"[s4-supervisor] checkpoint written: s4_bootstrap_started\")\n\n    # 5. Log success\n    print(f\"[s4-supervisor] foundation boot complete. sector_root={sr}\")\n\n    # 6. Exit cleanly (no operator dispatch in foundation phase)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) != 2:\n        raise SystemExit(\"usage: supervisor_shell.py <bootstrap_path>\")\n\n    run_supervisor(Path(sys.argv[1]))\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348128267}}
{"type":"message","id":"be763b6a","parentId":"c43c9d27","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:38.189Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Achei um sinal importante: o runtime ainda parece ter um `supervisor_shell.py` mínimo que só faz boot e sai. Vou agora verificar se o boundary real do S4 já chama o agente OpenClaw ou se ainda está preso nesse shell.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a3b7fc81918bceccd83744841b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MF4EcvKiaN6uZ1n8k0ToxBFK|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9aad1c48191a32225e263229b02","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"from pathlib import Path\nroot=Path(r'C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2')\nfor p in root.rglob('*.py'):\n    try:\n        txt=p.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\n    except Exception:\n        continue\n    if 'supervisor_shell.py' in txt or 's4_supervisor_bootstrap' in txt or 'sm_s4_asset_research' in txt or '_launch_openclaw_agent' in txt:\n        print('FILE', p)\n        for i,l in enumerate(txt.splitlines(),1):\n            if 'supervisor_shell.py' in l or 's4_supervisor_bootstrap' in l or 'sm_s4_asset_research' in l or '_launch_openclaw_agent' in l:\n                print(f'{i}: {l}')\n                \n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python -c \\\"from pathlib import Path\\nroot=Path(r'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2')\\nfor p in root.rglob('*.py'):\\n    try:\\n        txt=p.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\\n    except Exception:\\n        continue\\n    if 'supervisor_shell.py' in txt or 's4_supervisor_bootstrap' in txt or 'sm_s4_asset_research' in txt or '_launch_openclaw_agent' in txt:\\n        print('FILE', p)\\n        for i,l in enumerate(txt.splitlines(),1):\\n            if 'supervisor_shell.py' in l or 's4_supervisor_bootstrap' in l or 'sm_s4_asset_research' in l or '_launch_openclaw_agent' in l:\\n                print(f'{i}: {l}')\\n                \\n\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CD8D7GTPtQLjrxKeEg7L4BMe|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9aad1d081918076320a25b0c24a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\S4_invocation_spec.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4\\\\S4_invocation_spec.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_D2KiqZOnUEWrrepidgao2XvD|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9aad1d881918b12c38b6ca3296a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\S4_runtime_control_flow.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4\\\\S4_runtime_control_flow.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3540,"output":393,"cacheRead":32000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35933,"cost":{"input":0.00885,"output":0.005895,"cacheRead":0.008,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.022745}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775348128295,"responseId":"resp_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9a13ad48191aa650b3698b4bbd0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"97230df0","parentId":"be763b6a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:38.565Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MF4EcvKiaN6uZ1n8k0ToxBFK|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9aad1c48191a32225e263229b02","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"FILE C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\supervisor_shell.py\r\n46:         raise SystemExit(\"usage: supervisor_shell.py <bootstrap_path>\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":272,"aggregated":"FILE C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\supervisor_shell.py\r\n46:         raise SystemExit(\"usage: supervisor_shell.py <bootstrap_path>\")","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348138546}}
{"type":"message","id":"e78f45c9","parentId":"97230df0","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:38.584Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_CD8D7GTPtQLjrxKeEg7L4BMe|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9aad1d081918076320a25b0c24a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S4 — Invocation Specification\n\n_Status: planning draft_\n_Last updated: 2026-04-04_\n_Owner: Tobias_\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\nThis document freezes the **runtime invocation discipline** for S4.\n\nThe goal is to ensure S4 implementation does not rediscover the same failures already encountered in S3/B2 around:\n\n- process launching\n- timeouts\n- sessions\n- path drift\n- checkpoint observation\n- misleading exit codes\n- broken completion assumptions\n\nThis document is intentionally operational and repetitive. That is the point.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Canonical invocation primitive\n\nFor the current environment, the canonical invocation primitive remains:\n\n```text\nopenclaw agent --agent <agent_id> --message <task_or_contract_payload> --json --timeout <seconds> --session-id <unique_session_id>\n```\n\nFor Windows boundary/shell usage, the invocation must follow the same discipline already validated in B2/S3.\n\n### Operational interpretation\n\n- use non-blocking process launch where the boundary/supervisor should continue observing checkpoints\n- do not trust the exit code as truth\n- rely on checkpoint/artifact validation instead\n\n---\n\n## 3. Primary runtime rule\n\n### S4 v1 should use the proven S3/B2 invocation pattern\n\nThat means:\n\n- boundary/Python controls process lifecycle at the macro level\n- sector supervisor controls sector dispatch through the proven runtime substrate\n- operators do not become speculative process managers\n- no critical-path dependence on nested `sessions_spawn` announce chains\n\n---\n\n## 4. Mandatory invocation rules\n\n## Rule 1 — Unique session IDs always\n\nEvery agent invocation must use a unique session ID for the specific:\n\n- run\n- sector\n- actor\n- attempt / timestamp\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```text\n{job_id}__s4__{actor_id}__{timestamp}\n```\n\n### Why\n\nOpenClaw session accumulation is real.\nUnique session IDs reduce context pollution even before cleanup policy is applied.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 2 — Session cleanup before runs\n\nAll S4-related agent sessions must be cleaned before each fresh video run according to the same hygiene pattern already proven necessary in S3/B2.\n\nThis applies to at minimum:\n\n- `sm_s4_asset_research`\n- `op_s4_target_builder`\n- `op_s4_web_investigator`\n- `op_s4_target_research_worker`\n- `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n- `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n- `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\n### Why\n\nWithout cleanup:\n- stale context accumulates\n- agents silently degrade\n- prior video contamination becomes likely\n- cost inflates\n\n---\n\n## Rule 3 — `--json` required\n\nAll production-oriented invocations should use `--json`.\n\n### Why\n\nThis avoids ANSI noise and keeps runtime integration more parseable and consistent.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 4 — Explicit timeout required\n\nDo not rely on default timeouts.\n\nSuggested v1 timeout posture:\n\n- target builder: `--timeout 1800`\n- web investigator: `--timeout 1800`\n- target research worker: `--timeout 1800`\n- candidate evaluator: `--timeout 1800`\n- coverage analyst: `--timeout 1800`\n- pack compiler: `--timeout 1800`\n- sector supervisor: macro budget higher than per-operator runtime\n\nThese are planning defaults, not yet frozen implementation constants.\n\n### Why\n\nS3 already proved that default timeout assumptions are too fragile, and generous timeout budgets are safer than premature kill behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 5 — Absolute paths only in contracts\n\nEvery bootstrap, dispatch, checkpoint, and output contract must contain absolute paths.\n\n### Why\n\nRelative path drift already caused real failures in B2/S3.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 6 — ASCII-safe path discipline\n\nCritical runtime paths should avoid fragile special characters and rely on sanitized directory naming where appropriate.\n\n### Why\n\nPath encoding / Unicode drift is a real Windows risk in this environment.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 7 — stdout/stderr should not be treated as completion truth\n\nLogs are useful.\nThey are not authoritative completion signals.\n\nCompletion truth must come from:\n\n- checkpoint file existence\n- final artifact existence\n- contract validation\n\n---\n\n## Rule 8 — Process exit code is not completion truth\n\nEven if the CLI exits with a non-zero code, the boundary/supervisor should validate the on-disk artifacts before declaring failure.\n\n### Why\n\nThis was already a real S3/B2 lesson.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 9 — Settle time after checkpoint detection\n\nAfter detecting a critical checkpoint file, the watcher should wait a short settle interval before reading downstream artifacts.\n\nSuggested baseline:\n- ~2 seconds\n\n### Why\n\nFile flush timing can produce false premature reads.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 10 — Macro checkpoint mirroring is mandatory\n\nSector completion/failure must be mirrored into:\n\n```text\n{b2_root}/checkpoints/\n```\n\nThe boundary watches block-level checkpoints there.\n\n### Why\n\nWithout mirroring, the boundary may never observe sector completion correctly.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 11 — Use `subprocess.Popen`, not blocking `run()`, for boundary/supervisor orchestration\n\nThe runtime process primitive should be explicit:\n\n- use `subprocess.Popen` for launches that must continue while checkpoints are observed\n- do not use blocking `subprocess.run()` as the default orchestration primitive for long-running sector work\n\n### Why\n\nThis matches the proven S3/B2 behavior and avoids unnecessary blocking/kill coupling.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 12 — When launched from Claude Code / Paperclip-side automation, use detached shell discipline\n\nWhen relevant to the boundary-side launcher context, preserve detached execution discipline equivalent to the proven S3 guidance (for example `nohup` + `disown` on Unix-like environments).\n\n### Why\n\nThis prevents launcher termination from killing the agent process tree.\n\n### Windows note\n\nOn Windows, the analogous protection should be handled via the validated process creation flags and shell invocation pattern described below.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 13 — On Windows, invoke `.cmd` entrypoints with the proper shell pattern\n\nIf the launcher needs to execute a `.cmd` entrypoint in boundary Python / shell context, it must use the Windows-compatible invocation pattern equivalent to the already proven B2/S3 behavior.\n\nIn practical terms, the implementation must explicitly honor the Windows shell requirements rather than assuming Unix process semantics.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 14 — On Windows, use `CREATE_NEW_PROCESS_GROUP` or equivalent validated process-group isolation\n\nBoundary-side launches should preserve process-group isolation in line with the validated B2/S3 pattern.\n\n### Why\n\nThis reduces kill-chain coupling and gives the launcher better control over long-running sector processes.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 15 — Redirect stdout/stderr to log files, not PIPE or DEVNULL, for long-running launches\n\nFor long-running boundary/supervisor-controlled launches:\n\n- prefer dedicated log files\n- do not use PIPE as the default long-run capture mechanism\n- do not discard logs entirely via DEVNULL in production workflows\n\n### Why\n\nPIPE deadlocks and missing logs were already part of the S3/B2 lessons.\n\n---\n\n## Rule 16 — Boundary polling interval must be explicit\n\nThe boundary watcher should use an explicit checkpoint polling interval.\n\nSuggested baseline for v1:\n- 15 seconds, consistent with the proven S3 pattern unless a better validated value exists\n\n### Why\n\nPolling cadence is part of runtime semantics, not an incidental implementation detail.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Who dispatches whom in S4 v1\n\n## 5.1 Boundary-level responsibility\n\n`w3_block2.py` remains responsible for:\n\n- activating/resuming `b2_director`\n- observing block checkpoints\n- launching `sm_s4_asset_research` after detecting `s4_requested.json`\n- not micromanaging sector semantics\n\n## 5.2 Director-level responsibility\n\n`b2_director` remains responsible for:\n\n- requesting S4\n- writing/refreshing S4 bootstrap state\n- relying on the boundary to launch `sm_s4_asset_research`\n- resuming after `s4_completed` / `s4_failed`\n\n## 5.3 Sector-level responsibility\n\n`sm_s4_asset_research` remains responsible for sector dispatch.\n\nFor S4 v1, this means:\n\n- dispatching `op_s4_target_builder`\n- dispatching `op_s4_web_investigator`\n- dispatching `op_s4_target_research_worker` runs after briefs are written\n- dispatching `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n- dispatching `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n- dispatching `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\n### Important consequence\n\nEven though `op_s4_web_investigator` is the logical discovery coordinator, S4 v1 runtime does not require it to directly launch worker processes.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Actor-by-actor invocation expectations\n\n## 6.1 `sm_s4_asset_research`\n\nInvocation style:\n- launched by the boundary workflow after `s4_requested.json` and bootstrap are ready\n\nMust:\n- read bootstrap from disk\n- write dispatches/checkpoints to declared paths only\n- not absorb operator work as a substitute for dispatch\n\n## 6.2 `op_s4_target_builder`\n\nInvocation style:\n- dispatched by supervisor\n\nMust:\n- read dispatch artifact\n- write intake + report + status/checkpoint\n- not write outside sector-declared paths\n\n## 6.3 `op_s4_web_investigator`\n\nInvocation style:\n- dispatched by supervisor\n\nMust:\n- read intake + batch manifest\n- write target research briefs\n- write batch discovery planning artifact(s)\n- not be assumed to own runtime worker spawning in v1\n\n## 6.4 `op_s4_target_research_worker`\n\nInvocation style:\n- dispatched by supervisor after investigator briefs are available\n\nMust:\n- read one target brief\n- write candidate set + target-local files + checkpoint/status\n- remain a leaf node in v1 critical path\n\n## 6.5 `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n\nInvocation style:\n- dispatched by supervisor after candidate sets exist\n\nMust:\n- write evaluated candidate sets\n- not mutate upstream artifacts destructively\n\n## 6.6 `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n\nInvocation style:\n- dispatched by supervisor after evaluated candidate sets exist\n\nMust:\n- write coverage report\n\n## 6.7 `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\nInvocation style:\n- dispatched by supervisor after coverage report exists\n\nMust:\n- write final pack and sector report\n\n---\n\n## 7. Required checkpoints and status artifacts\n\nThe exact contract files will be frozen elsewhere, but invocation assumptions depend on these artifact families existing:\n\n### Boundary-owned / block-facing artifacts\n- `s4_requested.json`\n- mirrored `s4_completed.json` / `s4_failed.json`\n\n### Supervisor-owned sector runtime artifacts\n- bootstrap\n- dispatch log\n- sector status\n- sector checkpoint\n\n### Operator-owned artifacts\nPer operator/target phase:\n- status\n- checkpoint\n- output file(s)\n\n### Sector-final artifacts\n- `s4_research_pack.json`\n- `s4_sector_report.md`\n- `s4_completed.json` or `s4_failed.json`\n\n### Block-level mirrored artifacts\n- `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_completed.json`\n- `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_failed.json`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Prohibited assumptions\n\nFor S4 v1, do not assume any of the following unless explicitly validated later:\n\n- nested `sessions_spawn` is reliable enough for critical path orchestration\n- operator announce-back equals completion truth\n- operator exit code equals failure truth\n- workers can recursively create child workers in the critical path\n- missing files can be inferred from conversation summaries\n- sector completion can be accepted without report + final pack + checkpoint\n\n---\n\n## 9. Logging expectations\n\nLogs are useful for debugging but secondary to on-disk truth.\n\nRecommended practice:\n\n- each major invocation should have a dedicated log path\n- dispatch log should record what was launched and when\n- logs should support postmortem without becoming completion truth\n\n---\n\n## 10. Summary\n\nThe invocation spec for S4 v1 intentionally stays conservative:\n\n- preserve architectural richness\n- preserve separate evaluator and coverage analyst\n- preserve discovery coordination layer\n- but keep process control anchored to the proven B2/S3 invocation discipline\n\nThis is the operational basis for making the richer S4 architecture viable rather than magical.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348138567}}
{"type":"message","id":"487a80fa","parentId":"e78f45c9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:38.603Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_D2KiqZOnUEWrrepidgao2XvD|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9aad1d881918b12c38b6ca3296a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S4 — Runtime Control Flow\n\n_Status: planning draft_\n_Last updated: 2026-04-04_\n_Owner: Tobias_\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\nThis document freezes the **runtime control flow** for S4 — Asset Research.\n\nThe architecture document defines what S4 is and why it exists.\nThis document defines **how S4 actually progresses in runtime**, using the operational lessons already validated in B2/S3.\n\nThis document exists specifically to prevent three classes of failure:\n\n1. confusing logical hierarchy with runtime invocation hierarchy\n2. assuming nested agent spawning that has not been proven in this environment\n3. implementing S4 as a nice concept but a vague runtime\n\n---\n\n## 2. Central runtime decision\n\n### S4 v1 must follow the proven B2/S3 runtime pattern\n\nFor S4 v1, runtime orchestration must remain anchored to the already validated pattern:\n\n- filesystem-first truth\n- checkpoint-driven progression\n- boundary/Python-controlled orchestration\n- discrete agent activations\n- sector supervisor controlling sector dispatch\n- no dependency on nested `sessions_spawn` chains for critical path progression\n\n### Explicit consequence\n\nEven though the S4 architecture preserves a **discovery coordination layer** (`op_s4_web_investigator`), S4 v1 runtime should not depend on:\n\n- investigator agent directly spawning worker agents in the critical path\n- worker announce-backs as source of truth\n- recursive conversational orchestration\n\nInstead:\n\n- discovery coordination is expressed through artifacts\n- target workers are dispatched through the proven sector dispatch substrate\n- completion is determined via checkpoint files and artifact validation\n\n---\n\n## 3. Runtime actors\n\n### 3.1 `w3_block2.py` / boundary workflow\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- observe B2 checkpoints\n- activate/resume `b2_director`\n- launch `sm_s4_asset_research` after detecting `s4_requested.json`\n- remain the Paperclip-facing adapter\n- not make S4 semantic decisions internally\n\n### 3.2 `b2_director`\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- detect that S4 should start\n- create the S4 request checkpoint\n- write/refresh the S4 bootstrap payload\n- rely on the boundary workflow to launch the S4 supervisor\n- later resume on `s4_completed` / `s4_failed`\n\n### 3.3 `sm_s4_asset_research`\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- bootstrap the sector\n- validate upstream readiness\n- dispatch sector operators using the proven runtime primitive\n- validate artifacts\n- write sector and macro checkpoints\n- decide closure/degradation/failure\n\n### 3.4 S4 operators\n\n- `op_s4_target_builder`\n- `op_s4_web_investigator`\n- `op_s4_target_research_worker`\n- `op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n- `op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n- `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\nImportant:\n\n- operators are discrete runtime turns\n- outputs are persisted to disk\n- the sector supervisor resumes control between major phases\n\n---\n\n## 4. Canonical runtime sequence\n\n## Phase 0 — Upstream completion\n\n### Precondition\n\nS3 has completed and persisted at minimum:\n\n- `compiled_entities.json`\n- `s3_sector_report.md`\n- `s3_completed.json`\n\nThe B2 boundary/runtime has already validated that S3 ended in a resumable state.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Director requests S4\n\n### Actor\n`b2_director`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- current `b2_state.json`\n- `s3_completed.json`\n- validated S3 compiled artifact path\n\n### Actions\n\n1. validates S3 completion contract\n2. updates B2 state toward S4\n3. writes `s4_requested.json`\n4. writes/refreshes S4 bootstrap payload\n5. terminates after persisting the request-side state\n\n### Outputs\n\n- `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_requested.json`\n- updated `{b2_root}/state/b2_state.json`\n- sector bootstrap artifact under S4 runtime paths\n\n### Important rule\n\nIn the proven S3/B2 pattern, the director requests the sector.\nThe **boundary workflow** is then responsible for detecting the request checkpoint and launching the sector supervisor via the runtime process primitive.\n\nThe director should **not** become the runtime process spawner of the supervisor.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Boundary launches the S4 supervisor\n\n### Actor\n`w3_block2.py`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_requested.json`\n- S4 bootstrap artifact\n- updated `b2_state.json`\n\n### Actions\n\n1. detects `s4_requested.json`\n2. waits settle time before reading bootstrap/paths\n3. validates that the bootstrap artifact exists\n4. launches `sm_s4_asset_research` using the proven boundary runtime primitive\n5. returns to checkpoint observation mode\n\n### Outputs\n\n- process launch log\n- supervisor log path\n- boundary-side dispatch observation state\n\n### Important rule\n\nThis preserves the validated S3 pattern:\n\n- director writes request checkpoint\n- boundary launches supervisor\n- boundary later detects supervisor completion/failure checkpoint\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Supervisor bootstrap\n\n### Actor\n`sm_s4_asset_research`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- S4 bootstrap contract\n- S3 compiled artifact path\n- B2/S4 runtime roots\n\n### Actions\n\n1. validates bootstrap\n2. validates that upstream S3 artifact exists\n3. validates sector roots / paths\n4. assumes sector ownership\n5. writes sector working state\n6. prepares first operator dispatch (`op_s4_target_builder`)\n\n### Outputs\n\n- sector runtime status file\n- target-builder dispatch artifact\n- supervisor dispatch log entry\n\n### Important rule\n\nAt this stage the supervisor does **not** do target-building internally.\nIt dispatches the first operator.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — Target building\n\n### Actor\n`op_s4_target_builder`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- target-builder dispatch\n- `compiled_entities.json`\n- sector-local paths\n\n### Actions\n\n1. parses S3 compiled entities\n2. normalizes and deduplicates targets\n3. builds `scene_index`\n4. builds `research_targets`\n5. persists `s4_research_intake.json`\n6. writes `target_builder_report.md`\n7. writes operator status/checkpoint\n\n### Outputs\n\n- `intake/s4_research_intake.json`\n- `intake/target_builder_report.md`\n- operator checkpoint/status files\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5 — Intake validation and discovery planning\n\n### Actor\n`sm_s4_asset_research`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- `s4_research_intake.json`\n- target-builder checkpoint/status\n\n### Actions\n\n1. validates target-builder success\n2. validates intake schema\n3. validates minimum target sufficiency\n4. writes `research_batch_manifest.json`\n5. dispatches `op_s4_web_investigator`\n\n### Outputs\n\n- `batches/research_batch_manifest.json`\n- investigator dispatch artifact\n\n### Important rule\n\nThe supervisor governs the phase transition.\nThe supervisor does **not** manually invent briefs in chat memory.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6 — Discovery brief generation\n\n### Actor\n`op_s4_web_investigator`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- `s4_research_intake.json`\n- `research_batch_manifest.json`\n\n### Actions\n\n1. reads active targets/batches\n2. transforms them into bounded target research briefs\n3. writes one `target_research_brief.json` per target or target-batch\n4. optionally writes a batch discovery summary artifact\n5. marks discovery brief generation complete\n\n### Outputs\n\nPer target:\n- `targets/<target_id>/target_research_brief.json`\n\nOptional batch artifact:\n- `batches/batch_001_discovery_summary.json`\n\n### Critical runtime note\n\nFor S4 v1, this actor should **not** be assumed to directly spawn workers.\nIt writes the discovery-control artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7 — Target-worker dispatch\n\n### Actor\n`sm_s4_asset_research`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- worker brief files produced by investigator\n- `research_batch_manifest.json`\n\n### Actions\n\n1. validates that the expected research briefs exist\n2. determines which worker runs to dispatch now\n3. dispatches `op_s4_target_research_worker` invocations using the proven runtime primitive\n4. tracks expected worker outputs in dispatch/runtime status\n\n### Outputs\n\n- worker dispatch artifacts\n- updated supervisor runtime state\n\n### Important runtime decision\n\nThis is the key flattening of invocation hierarchy while preserving logical richness:\n\n- investigator coordinates discovery **logically**\n- supervisor dispatches workers **operationally**\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8 — Target research execution\n\n### Actor\n`op_s4_target_research_worker`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- target research brief\n- target-local output paths\n\n### Actions\n\n1. performs bounded discovery for that target\n2. collects candidates\n3. materializes files when appropriate\n4. writes `candidate_set.json`\n5. writes local files under `assets/`, `previews/`, `captures/`\n6. writes worker status/checkpoint\n\n### Outputs\n\nPer target:\n- `candidate_set.json`\n- local files\n- worker checkpoint/status\n\n### Important runtime note\n\nWorkers are leaf nodes for S4 v1.\nThey do not recursively dispatch further agents in the critical path.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9 — Worker completion validation\n\n### Actor\n`sm_s4_asset_research`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- worker checkpoints/status files\n- expected worker dispatch list\n- optional batch discovery summaries\n\n### Actions\n\n1. validates that required worker runs finished\n2. validates that expected candidate sets exist\n3. validates that minimum local artifacts exist where required\n4. decides whether the discovery phase is sufficiently complete for v1\n5. dispatches evaluator\n\n### Outputs\n\n- evaluator dispatch artifact\n- updated supervisor runtime state\n\n### S4 v1 policy\n\nBy default:\n- one strong pass\n- no automatic second-round redispatch in baseline runtime\n\nIf some targets fail, the supervisor should handle that through coverage semantics / degradation policy rather than assuming recursive redispatch by default.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10 — Candidate evaluation\n\n### Actor\n`op_s4_candidate_evaluator`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- all target candidate sets\n- target briefs\n- local files/previews/captures\n\n### Actions\n\n1. evaluates candidates per target\n2. confirms/corrects classification\n3. marks best candidates\n4. marks usability of local files/previews\n5. writes `evaluated_candidate_set.json` per target\n\n### Outputs\n\nPer target:\n- `evaluated_candidate_set.json`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11 — Coverage analysis\n\n### Actor\n`op_s4_coverage_analyst`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- `s4_research_intake.json`\n- evaluated candidate sets\n\n### Actions\n\n1. computes target-level coverage\n2. computes scene-level coverage\n3. identifies unresolved gaps\n4. writes `coverage_report.json`\n\n### Outputs\n\n- `compiled/coverage_report.json`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 12 — Pack compilation\n\n### Actor\n`sm_s4_asset_research` then `op_s4_pack_compiler`\n\n### Supervisor actions\n\n1. validates evaluator and coverage outputs\n2. dispatches compiler\n\n### Compiler actions\n\n1. reads all final sector artifacts\n2. builds `s4_research_pack.json`\n3. builds `s4_sector_report.md`\n4. writes compiler checkpoint/status\n\n### Outputs\n\n- `compiled/s4_research_pack.json`\n- `compiled/s4_sector_report.md`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 13 — Sector closure\n\n### Actor\n`sm_s4_asset_research`\n\n### Inputs\n\n- compiler outputs\n- sector runtime state\n\n### Actions\n\n1. validates final pack exists\n2. validates sector report exists\n3. writes sector completion or failure checkpoint\n4. mirrors macro checkpoint into B2 checkpoints\n5. updates sector status/state\n\n### Outputs\n\nAt minimum:\n- `{sector_root}/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` or `s4_failed.json`\n- `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` or `s4_failed.json`\n\n### Critical rule\n\nS4 does not count as completed without both:\n\n- final compiled artifact\n- sector report\n\n---\n\n## Phase 14 — Director resume\n\n### Actor\n`w3_block2.py` then `b2_director`\n\n### Boundary actions\n\n1. detects `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` or `s4_failed.json`\n2. waits settle time\n3. resumes `b2_director`\n\n### Director actions\n\n1. validates S4 completion/failure contract\n2. decides next transition (normally S5)\n3. updates B2 state\n\n---\n\n## 5. Runtime truth model\n\n### 5.1 Disk is the source of truth\n\nThe runtime truth model for S4 must match B2/S3:\n\n- files on disk are primary truth\n- conversational summaries are secondary evidence only\n- process exit code is not completion truth\n- checkpoint presence plus artifact validation determines sector progression\n\n### 5.2 No live-memory dependence\n\nS4 should not depend on:\n\n- long-lived chat memory between actors\n- implicit sibling awareness\n- unpersisted “mental notes” across activations\n\nAll meaningful phase transitions must be artifact-backed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Proposed S4 state machine\n\n### 6.1 Sector runtime states and checkpoint/file mapping\n\nSuggested sector states:\n\n| State | Primary artifact / checkpoint | Writer | Reader |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `s4_bootstrap_started` | S4 bootstrap artifact | `b2_director` | `w3_block2.py`, `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_requested` | `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_requested.json` | `b2_director` | `w3_block2.py` |\n| `s4_target_building` | target-builder dispatch artifact | `sm_s4_asset_research` | `op_s4_target_builder` |\n| `s4_intake_ready` | `intake/s4_research_intake.json` | `op_s4_target_builder` | `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_discovery_planning` | `batches/research_batch_manifest.json` | `sm_s4_asset_research` | `op_s4_web_investigator` |\n| `s4_briefs_ready` | `targets/<target_id>/target_research_brief.json` (+ optional batch summary) | `op_s4_web_investigator` | `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_target_research_running` | worker dispatch + worker status/checkpoints | `sm_s4_asset_research` / workers | `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_candidate_evaluation_running` | evaluator dispatch + evaluated outputs | `sm_s4_asset_research` / evaluator | `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_coverage_analysis_running` | coverage analyst dispatch + `compiled/coverage_report.json` | `sm_s4_asset_research` / coverage analyst | `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_pack_compilation_running` | compiler dispatch + final pack/report generation | `sm_s4_asset_research` / compiler | `sm_s4_asset_research` |\n| `s4_completed` | `{sector_root}/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` + mirrored `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_completed.json` | `sm_s4_asset_research` | `w3_block2.py`, `b2_director` |\n| `s4_failed` | `{sector_root}/checkpoints/s4_failed.json` + mirrored `{b2_root}/checkpoints/s4_failed.json` | `sm_s4_asset_research` | `w3_block2.py`, `b2_director` |\n| `s4_degraded_completed` | optional degraded completion checkpoint if explicitly adopted later | `sm_s4_asset_research` | `w3_block2.py`, `b2_director` |\n\n### 6.2 Recommended v1 completion policy\n\nFor S4 v1, prefer:\n\n- `completed`\n- `failed`\n\nUse `degraded_completed` only if intentionally and explicitly justified.\nIt should not become a vague default closure bucket.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Core runtime risks\n\n### 7.1 Risk: logical hierarchy gets mistaken for nested runtime spawning\n\nMitigation:\n- freeze the dispatch model explicitly\n- require supervisor / boundary controlled worker launches in v1\n\n### 7.2 Risk: worker explosion\n\nMitigation:\n- batch manifest with explicit parallelism caps\n- target workers as bounded leaf runs\n- freeze a v1 parallelism cap before implementation (for example 3 concurrent target workers)\n\n### 7.3 Risk: sector stalls on missing target outputs\n\nMitigation:\n- explicit expected worker manifest\n- checkpoint validation by supervisor\n- closure policy defined in advance\n\n### 7.4 Risk: completion not observed by B2 boundary\n\nMitigation:\n- macro checkpoint mirroring into `{b2_root}/checkpoints/`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Summary\n\nS4 v1 preserves the rich sector design but operationalizes it through the already proven Block 2 runtime principles:\n\n- state machine on disk\n- checkpoint-driven progression\n- boundary/python controlled orchestration\n- supervisor-controlled sector dispatch\n- artifact-based discovery coordination\n- target workers as leaf-node executions\n- evaluator and coverage analyst kept separate\n- no mandatory second round in baseline v1\n\nThis is the intended runtime baseline for planning, documentation review, and later implementation.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775348138584}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8b877fa","parentId":"487a80fa","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:48.853Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_O1Iiwz7FwAVNc20D09un82hq|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9b57e3c8191a2cd29aebdddb93a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import os\nroot=r'C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4'\nfor dp,_,fs in os.walk(root):\n    for f in fs:\n        if f.endswith('.py'):\n            p=os.path.join(dp,f)\n            try: txt=open(p,'r',encoding='utf-8').read()\n            except Exception: continue\n            if 'openclaw agent' in txt or 'subprocess.Popen' in txt or 'subprocess.run' in txt:\n                print(p)\n                for i,l in enumerate(txt.splitlines(),1):\n                    if 'openclaw agent' in l or 'subprocess.Popen' in l or 'subprocess.run' in l:\n                        print(f'{i}: {l}')\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python -c \\\"import os\\nroot=r'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4'\\nfor dp,_,fs in os.walk(root):\\n    for f in fs:\\n        if f.endswith('.py'):\\n            p=os.path.join(dp,f)\\n            try: txt=open(p,'r',encoding='utf-8').read()\\n            except Exception: continue\\n            if 'openclaw agent' in txt or 'subprocess.Popen' in txt or 'subprocess.run' in txt:\\n                print(p)\\n                for i,l in enumerate(txt.splitlines(),1):\\n                    if 'openclaw agent' in l or 'subprocess.Popen' in l or 'subprocess.run' in l:\\n                        print(f'{i}: {l}')\\n\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Scir1KSAxaXz8nKyh7e67dVN|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9b57e5c8191a017b21cb33d38f8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"from pathlib import Path\np=Path(r'C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\artifact_io.py')\nprint(p.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python -c \\\"from pathlib import Path\\np=Path(r'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4\\\\helpers\\\\artifact_io.py')\\nprint(p.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\\n\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JuMt3X3jDMSkFuJuM7DCvq8x|fc_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9b57e648191b696717876c223c3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"from pathlib import Path\np=Path(r'C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S4\\helpers\\paths.py')\nprint(p.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python -c \\\"from pathlib import Path\\np=Path(r'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S4\\\\helpers\\\\paths.py')\\nprint(p.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\\n\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":6335,"output":421,"cacheRead":35840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42596,"cost":{"input":0.0158375,"output":0.006315,"cacheRead":0.00896,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0311125}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775348138603,"responseId":"resp_05bdd3a20628929c0169d1a9ab83ac81919484547ceb236653"}}
